quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  42,23,"Such is God‘s joyful promise to His servants who believe and do good works. Say: ‘For this I ask of you no recompense, except to love your kin. He that does a good deed We shall repay many times over. Surely God is forgiving and bountiful in His rewards.‘"
  42,24,"Or do they say: ‘He has framed a falsehood about God?‘ But if God pleased, He could set a seal upon your heart. God will bring falsehood to nothing and vindicate the Truth by His Words. He surely knows ones innermost thoughts"
  42,25,"He it is who accepts His servants‘ repentance, and pardons their sins. He has knowledge of what you do"
  42,26,"And He answers those who believe and do good works, and enriches them through His bounty. But grievous punishment awaits the unbelievers"
  42,27,"Had God bestowed abundance upon His servants, they would have committed much injustice in the land. But He gives what He will in due measure; He well knows and observes His servants"
  42,28,"He it is who sends down the rain when they have lost all hope, and spreads abroad His mercy. He is the Guardian worthy of praise"
  42,29,"Among His signs is the creation of the heavens and the earth and the living things He has dispersed over them. If He will, He can gather them all together"
  42,30,"Whatever misfortune befalls you, it is the fruit of your own labours. He forgives much"
  42,31,"And on the earth you cannot escape, nor have you any besides God to protect or help you"